# Copy to agent/.env and adjust. Loaded by `make run-agent`, `make run-agent-tui`,
# and `make run-agent-web`.
# This file is the agent's config only — the daemon does not read it and never
# needs the LLM API key.

# Model the agent uses, as provider:model (required by `make run-agent`).
# Providers: anthropic, openai, google, ollama (local), llamacpp (local).
CODEBERG_MODEL=anthropic:claude-haiku-4-5

# Daemon the agent queries over HTTP (default: http://127.0.0.1:48080)
# CODEBERG_DAEMON_URL=http://127.0.0.1:48080

# Reasoning effort for reasoning-capable models (ai-sdk v7 `reasoning` control):
# provider-default | none | minimal | low | medium | high | xhigh
# CODEBERG_REASONING=medium

# --- external providers (set the API key matching CODEBERG_MODEL) -----------
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=

# --- ollama (local) ---------------------------------------------------------
# Local Ollama needs no API key. Set CODEBERG_MODEL=ollama:<model>, e.g.
# ollama:qwen3.5:9b (run `ollama list` for the exact tag). Override the
# endpoint only if Ollama is not on the default host/port:
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1

# --- llama.cpp (local) ------------------------------------------------------
# A running llama-server (OpenAI-compatible API). No API key needed. The model
# id is a free-form label — llama-server serves whatever was loaded with `-m`,
# so e.g. CODEBERG_MODEL=llamacpp:ornith-1.0-35b. Override the endpoint if
# llama-server is not on its default port 8080 (e.g. --port 11434):
# LLAMACPP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/v1

# --- web access (web_search + fetch_url) ------------------------------------
# The agent can read web pages (fetch_url) and search the web (web_search).
# On by default; disable all web access with:
# CODEBERG_WEB_USE=false
#
# web_search uses SearXNG (open-source, no API key). When run via the `codeberg`
# launcher, a local instance is installed and managed for you — no setup needed.
# To point at your own SearXNG instead (the launcher then won't manage one), set:
# CODEBERG_SEARXNG_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8888
#
# fetch_url blocks localhost/private hosts by default (SSRF guard). Allow them
# (e.g. to read an internal docs server) with:
# CODEBERG_WEB_ALLOW_PRIVATE=1
#
# Tuning (sensible defaults otherwise):
# CODEBERG_WEB_MAX_CHARS=20000      # max extracted text per page
# CODEBERG_WEB_TIMEOUT_MS=15000     # per-request timeout
# CODEBERG_WEB_SEARCH_COUNT=6       # default results per web_search
